    <text>
        <body>
            <div1 type="calendarCollection">
                <!--div1 just wraps the whole collection. -->
                
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-01-30"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/february/1909-01-30.jpg">
                    
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab rend="print" hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-01-30"> January 30, 1909. <lb/>Saturday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure rend="cutout" hand="#blackpen">
                        <figDesc resp="#acolemanreeves"> A man with a mustache laying in bad.
                            
                        </figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil" rend="cursive"> E.R.B.
                    <lb/>"That damned old clock
                    <lb/>gives me a</ab>
                </div2>
                
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-02-16"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/february/1909-02-16.jpg">
                    
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab rend="print" hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-02-16"> February 16, 1909. <lb/>Tuesday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure rend="color" hand="#multicolor">
                        <figDesc resp="#acolemanreeves"> <persName>Mr Behrend</persName> holding a large bug.
                         
                        </figDesc>
                    </figure>
                        <ab hand="#pencil" rend="cursive"> <persName>Mr. Behrend</persName> finds a 
                            <lb/> big bug!</ab>
                        <ab hand="#redPen" rend="cursive"> I wonder if you have found many lately</ab>
                </div2>
                
                
                
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-02-17"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/february/1909-02-17.jpg">
                    
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-02-17">February 17, 1909. <lb/>Wednesday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure><figDesc resp="#acolereeves"></figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil" rend="#cursive">
                        <lb/> Each morning very early <lb/> When all is dark and still<lb/> <persName>Ernst</persName> goes off into likely blackness <lb/>To work at Hammermill <lb/> I really think he's very good <lb/>to get up when it's dark <lb/> tho he says he doesn't mind <lb/> It cant (blank) (blank) a lark!
                    </ab>
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" place="bottom-right">(blank) is it still dark when you arise?</add></ab>
                </div2>
                
                
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-08"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/march/1909-03-08.jpg">
                    
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-08">March 8, 1909. <lb/>Monday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#redink">
                        <figDesc resp="#acolemanreeves">A large question mark in the center of the paper.</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                   <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" place="bottom-right">.. this is the day, this...later. done. the</add></ab> <!-- finish trasncribing here -->
                </div2>
                
                
                
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-12"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/march/1909-03-12.jpg">
                    
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-12">March 12, 1909. <lb/>Friday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#multicolor">
                        <figDesc resp="#acolemanreeves">Drawing of a woman in snowshoes named <persName>Molly</persName> pointing
                            ahead of her. This is along the left-hand side of the page.</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil">
                        <lb/><persName>Molly</persName> on <lb/>snowshoes <lb/>that <persName>Mr. Weir</persName> <lb/>got. <lb/>Pretty picture
                        <lb/>is it not?!</ab>
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" place="bottom-right">Love from <persName>Molly</persName></add></ab>
                </div2>
                
                
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-17"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/march/1909-03-17.jpg">
                    
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-17">March 17, 1909. <lb/>Wednesday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#brownink">
                        <figDesc resp="#acolemanreeves"> Green Shamrocks dispersed throughout the paper. Two <rs type="animal">snakes</rs> drawn on the top of the paper. A drawing of the hammermill center bottom right corner. </figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#brownink">
                        <lb/><persName>ST. Patrick</persName> was a useful saint<lb/> He frightened all the snakes away- <lb/>I wish he'd try his art on smoke  <lb/>around the hammermill some day! 
                        <lb/>is it not?!</ab>
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" >The Hammermill really lucky!</add></ab>  <!-- finish trasncribing here -->
                </div2>
                
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-23"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/march/1909-03-23.jpg">
                    
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-23">March 23, 1909. <lb/>Tuesday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#pencil">
                        <figDesc resp="#acolemanreeves">Drawing of clothes hanging up to dry.</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil">
                        <lb/>Wash day at <persName>the behrends</persName> <lb/>oh, I say! <lb/>That's really a very  <lb/>unusual display! 
                    </ab>
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" place="bottom-right">Do you still miss me?</add></ab> 
                </div2>
                
                
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-25"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/march/1909-03-25.jpg">
                    
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-25">March 25, 1909. <lb/>Thursday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#multicolor">
                        <figDesc resp="#acolemanreeves">A woman walking in a garden</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil">
                        <title> At the Lavers </title>
                        <lb/>"Ill send the bill to <persName>Ernst</persName> <lb/> and take them every one <lb/>I'll watch his face &amp;see him <lb/>smile <lb/>It will be such jolly fun!"
                    </ab> 
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" place="top-right"><persName>Molly</persName> reviewing a full Gig bill Poor <persName>Ernst</persName></add></ab> <!-- finish trasncribing here -->
                </div2>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
